The paper proposes a method for predicting mercury content in the output gas of power station boilers using adaptive neuro fuzzy inference system (ANFIS) method integrated with particle swarm optimization (PSO). This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper deals with the prediction of environmental pollution, which could fall under the sub-category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
